<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He appeared on the 2006 series of I'm A Celeb, and the 2011 series of Strictly. </p>

<p>And now Jason Donovan is ready for his next dose of reality TV as he is reportedly one of the stars competing on the upcoming series of Dancing On Ice. </p>

<p>The former Neighbours heartthrob, 52 - who competed on Strictly in 2011 - is expected to join the star-studded line-up on the ITV show which takes place in January 2021. </p>

<p>Competition time: Jason Donovan is ready for his next dose of reality TV as he is reportedly one of the stars competing on the upcoming series of Dancing On Ice (pictured 2018)</p>

<p>A source told The Sun: 'Jason is a great signing for the show as he has plenty of star power.</p>

<p>'He knows how to dance but if he thinks it’ll be any help once he’s on the ice he has another thing coming.</p>

<p>'He’s hoping to rank higher in this show than he did on Strictly, he just needs to find out if he can stay upright once he has his skates on.'</p>

<p>Star power: The former Neighbours heartthrob, 52, is scheduled to join the star-studded line-up for the ITV show which takes place in January 2021 according to The Sun (above 2020 winner Joe Swash with partner Alex Murphy)</p>

<p>Sensation: Jason appeared on the 2011 series of Strictly Come Dancing alongside pro Kristina Rihanoff</p>

<p>Especially for you: Jason is known for his role as Scott Robinson in Neighbours alongside Kylie Minogue before the pair launched singing careers (pictured 1980s)</p>

<p>According to the insider, studio executives are excited about the big names that will grace the ice rink for the upcoming series. </p>

<p>MailOnline has contacted representatives for Jason Donovan and Dancing On Ice for comment. </p>

<p>Made In Chelsea's Olivia Bentley, TOWIE's Billie Faiers and Love Island's Luke Trotman are among the celebrities vying for a spot on the Dancing On Ice after they were spotted attending an audition in July. </p>

<p>Denise van Outen, is believed to have inked a £40,000 deal to appear on the next series while Rebekah Vardy has allegedly landed £50,000 for her upcoming participation. </p>

<p>The Sun reports that Olympic sprint legend Colin Jackson, 53, has also signed up for the show. Representative for the sportsman have been contacted by MailOnline. </p>

<p>Fast: The Sun also reports that Olympic sprint legend Colin Jackson, 53, has also signed up for the show (pictured 2003)</p>

<p>Get your skates on: Rebekah Vardy has allegedly landed £50,000 to participate on the show amid her ongoing £1 million court battle with fellow WAG Coleen Rooney</p>

<p>The WAG, 38, is in the midst of a £1 million court battle with Coleen Rooney, 34, but is now said to have set her sights on the reality competition.</p>

<p>A source told the website that Rebekah's footballer husband Jamie will be on the sidelines to support her.</p>

<p>MailOnline has contacted Becky's representatives for comment, Dancing On Ice spokesmen declined to comment when approached. </p>

<p>Ready for the rink: Denise Van Outen is also believed to have inked a £40,000 deal to appear on the next series of Dancing On Ice</p>
